A 33-year-old man drowned at Witsand on the Southern Cape coast after being caught in a rip current on Saturday afternoon, the National Sea Rescue Institute (NSRI) said.NSRI Witsand duty crew were activated at about 4pm following reports of a man missing in the surf line in front of the Anchorage Beach, Witsand, NSRI Witsand station commander Theo Erasmus said.NSRI rescue swimmers responded to the scene and were deployed into the surf to begin a search for the 33-year-old local man who had reportedly disappeared under water in the surf line after being swept out to sea by rip currents while swimming.The NSRI launched the sea rescue craft Breede Rescuer to join in the search and the SA Police Service, Western Cape government health emergency medical services (EMS), a police dive unit, and a local doctor responded to assist.&#8220;During a search, the body of the man was located and recovered from shallow surf and cardiopulmonary resuscitation (CPR) efforts were commenced but after all efforts to resuscitate the man were exhausted he was declared deceased by the doctor.Sincerest condolences are conveyed to the family of the deceased man,&#8221; Erasmus said.-SABC